-- Italian Commercial Vehicle Sales Rose 3.7% in June, Iveco Deliveries Gain
-- Tommaso Ebhardt
-- 2010-07-07T10:14:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/italian-commercial-vehicle-sales-rose-3-7-in-june-iveco-deliveries-gain.html

          
          
             Italian light-vehicle sales rose 3.7
percent in June to 16,703 units, carmakers’ associations Anfia
and Unrae said today in a e-mailed statement.  
 Fiat SpA’s deliveries of vans rose 12.4 percent to 7,352
units, while the Turin, Italy-based company’s Iveco unit posted
a 8.6 percent increase to 1,424 units.  
          
          


  


        